                        "displayName": "Weston Pace",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
                    },
                    "body": "I think you are trying to overwrite a file that you are currently reading.  What would be the preferred result here?  Should it be an error before the write begins?  Should it detect that the filename already exists and use a different filename?  Is there some other preferred outcome?\r\n\r\nI think you get away with it when the dataset is smaller because all the data fits onto a single batch so by the time you start writing you have already finished reading.",
